Let $A =
        \begin{pmatrix}
        e^{2x} & -1  \\
        0 & e^{2x}-1  \\
        \end{pmatrix}
$. Compute $A^7$. I've tried the obvious way of multiplying $A$ with $A$, then $A^2$ with $A^2$, but I arrived at a messy result in the top right member of the matrix. Is there a general form to be noticed here?
